{"title_page": "Guillermo Brown de Puerto Madryn", "text_new": "{{Other uses|Football clubs named after Almirante Brown}}\n{{Infobox football club\n| clubname = Guillermo Brown\n| image = Guill brown arg.png\n| image_size = 130px\n| fullname = Club Social y Atl\u00e9tico Guillermo Brown\n| nickname = ''La Banda'', ''Capo Del Sur''<br> ''La Banda del Sur''\n| founded  = January 14, 1945| \n| ground   = [[Estadio Raul Conti]], [[Puerto Madryn]]<br>[[Chubut Province|Chubut]], [[Argentina]]\n| capacity = 12,500\n| chairman = Carlos Eliceche\n| manager  = Marcelo Broggi\n| league   = [[Primera B Nacional]]\n| season   = [[2018\u201319 Primera B Nacional|2018\u201319]]\n| position = 20th\n| current  = 2019\u201320 Guillermo Brown de Puerto Madryn season\n|pattern_la1=_gbm1112h|pattern_b1=_gbm1112h|pattern_ra1=_gbm1112h|leftarm1=FFFFFF|body1=FFFFFF|rightarm1=FFFFFF|shorts1=FFFFFF|socks1=FFFFFF\n|pattern_la2=_gbm1112a|pattern_b2=_gbm1112a|pattern_ra2=_gbm1112a|leftarm2=FFFFFF|body2=FFFFFF|rightarm2=FFFFFF|shorts2=000080|socks2=000080\n|pattern_la3=_gbm1112t|pattern_b3=_gbm1112t|pattern_ra3=_gbm1112t|leftarm3=000080|body3=000080|rightarm3=000080|shorts3=000080|socks3=000080\n}}\n\n'''Club Social y Atl\u00e9tico Guillermo Brown''', mostly known as '''Guillermo Brown''' or  '''Brown de Puerto Madryn''', is an [[Argentina|Argentine]] [[sports club]] from [[Puerto Madryn]] in [[Chubut Province]]. The football team currently plays in the [[Primera B Nacional]].\n\n==History==\nThe club was named in honour of [[William Brown (admiral)|Guillermo Brown]] who was the Irish-born first admiral of Argentina in the mid 19th Century.\n\nBrown finished at the top of their group in the Torneo Clausura 2006, but failed in the next stage, after being defeated by [[Club Atl\u00e9tico San Mart\u00edn (Tucum\u00e1n)|San Mart\u00edn de Tucum\u00e1n]] in the playoff series (with scores of 0\u20133 and 2\u20132).\n\nOn May 19, 2012, Brown achieved its greatest professional achievement in football, tying 2\u20132 at [[Estadio Monumental Antonio Vespucio Liberti|River Plate Stadium]] against a [[Club Atletico River Plate|River Plate]] with figures such as [[David Trezeguet]], [[Fernando Cavenaghi]] and [[Alejandro Dami\u00e1n Dom\u00ednguez|Alejandro Dominguez]].\n\n==Current squad==\n''As of September 12, 2019''<ref>[https://nr.soccerway.com/teams/argentina/atletico-guillermo-brown/7054/squad/ Guillermo Brown squad], soccerway.com</ref>\n{{Fs start}}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=ARG |pos=GK |name= Franco Ag\u00fcero}}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=ARG |pos=GK |name= Braian Maya}}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=ARG |pos=GK |name= [[C\u00e9sar Taborda]]}}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=ARG |pos=DF |name= [[Mauro Baz\u00e1n]]}}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=ARG |pos=DF |name= [[Kevin Ceceri]]}}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=ARG |pos=DF |name= [[Guillermo Ferracuti]]}}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=ARG |pos=DF |name= [[Diego Herner]]}}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=ARG |pos=DF |name= [[Leandro Lugarzo]]}}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=ARG |pos=DF |name= [[Mauro Osores]]|other=<small>on loan from [[Atl\u00e9tico Tucum\u00e1n]]}}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=ARG |pos=DF |name= Fabrizio Romero}}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=ARG |pos=DF |name= [[Mat\u00edas Ru\u00edz D\u00edaz]]|other=<small>on loan from [[Estudiantes de La Plata|Estudiantes]]}}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=ARG |pos=DF |name= [[Luciano S\u00e1nchez (footballer, born September 1994)|Luciano S\u00e1nchez]]}}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=ARG |pos=MF |name= Carlos \u00c1vila}}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=ARG |pos=MF |name= Elian Coronas}}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=ARG |pos=MF |name= Mauro Cort\u00e9z}}\n{{Fs mid}}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=ARG |pos=MF |name= [[Rodrigo Depetris]]}}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=ARG |pos=MF |name= [[Cristian Garc\u00eda (footballer, born 1996)|Cristian Garc\u00eda]]}}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=ARG |pos=MF |name= Cristian Lobo}}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=ARG |pos=MF |name= [[Emanuel Moreno]]}}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=URU |pos=MF |name= Cristian Muga}}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=ARG |pos=MF |name= [[Mateo Ram\u