6648/fullcredits |title= First Impressions with Dana Carvey Full Cast & Crew |website=[[IMDb]] |access-date=November 26, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2016{{en dash}}present\n| ''[[Saturday Night Live]]''\n| Herself/various\n| 69 episodes\n|<ref name=Jones20160912 /><ref name=Blair20180929 />\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Jeff & Some Aliens]]''\n| Julie, Adele (voice)\n| Episode: \"Jeff & Some Preteen Girls\"\n|<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt4218824/fullcredits |title=Jeff & Some Aliens (2017)  |website=[[IMDb]] |access-date=November 26, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[F Is for Family]]''\n| Additional voices\n| 2 episodes\n|<ref name=Haring20180614 />\n|-\n| 2017{{en dash}}19\n| ''[[OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes]]''\n| Various voices\n| 13 episodes\n|<ref name=Blair20180929 />\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[The David S. Pumpkins Halloween Special]]''\n| Additional voices\n| Television Special\n|<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt7452910/fullcredits |title=The David S. Pumpkins Halloween Special (2017) Full Cast & Crew |website=[[IMDb]] |access-date=November 26, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''[[Crashing (U.S. TV series)|Crashing]]''\n| Herself\n| Episode: \"NACA\"\n|<ref name=White20180226 />\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''[[Barry (TV series)|Barry]]''\n| Waitress\n| Episode: \"[[Chapter One: Make Your Mark]]\"\n|<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.spin.com/2018/03/hbo-barry-review/ |title=HBO's Barry Plays on the Subtler Charms of Bill Hader |last=Serota |first=Maggie |date=March 26, 2018 |website=[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]] |access-date=November 24, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2018\u201319\n| ''[[American Dad!]]''\n| Various voices\n| 2 episodes\n|<ref name=\"Haring20180614\">{{Cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/06/snls-melissa-villasenor-signs-with-wme-for-representation-in-all-areas-1202410991/ |title=SNL's Melissa Villase\u00f1or Signs With WME |last=Haring |first=Bruce |date=June 14, 2018 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |access-date=November 24, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[Comedians in Cars Getting Coffee]]''\n| Herself\n| Episode: \"Melissa Villase\u00f1or\"\n|<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.newsday.com/entertainment/tv/comedians-in-cars-getting-coffee-review-1.34016598 |title='Comedians in Cars Getting Coffee' review: Affable entertainment from Jerry Seinfeld and pals |last=Guzm\u00e1n |first=Rafer |date=July 19, 2019 |website=[[Newsday]] |access-date=November 24, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2020 \n| ''[[Awkwafina is Nora from Queens]]''\n| Performer\n| Episode: Paperwork \n|<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm3830257/?ref_=tt_cl_t2|title=Internet Movie Database|date=March 10, 2020 |website=[[IMDB]] |access-date=March 10, 2020}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n* {{Official website}}\n* {{IMDb name|3830257}}\n\n{{SNLCurrentCast}}\n{{America's Got Talent}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Villasenor, Melissa}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:Actresses from California]]\n[[Category:American actresses of Mexican descent]]\n[[Category:American impressionists (entertainers)]]\n[[Category:American sketch comedians]]\n[[Category:American stand-up comedians]]\n[[Category:American voice actresses]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:American women comedians]]\n[[Category:Comedians from California]]\n[[Category:Hispanic and Latino American actresses]]\n[[Category:People from Whittier, California]]\n[[Category:21st-century American comedians]]\n", "text_old": "{{pp-pc|small=yes}}\n{{short description|American comedian/actress}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=September 2016}}\n{{Infobox comedian\n| name        = Melissa Villase\u00f1or\n| image       = Melissa Villasenor (Sad People Talking) 6843626905.jpg\n| caption     = Villase\u00f1or in [[Los Angeles, California]] in February 2012\n| birth_name  =\n| birth_date  =\n| birth_place = [[Whittier, California]], U.S.\n| death_date  =\n| death_place =\n| medium      = Stand-up, film, television, music, art\n| years_active = 2010\u2013present \n| nationality = American\n| active      =\n| genre       =\n| subject     =\n| influences  =\n| website     = {{URL|http://melissavillasenor.com/}}\n}}\n\n'''Melissa Villase\u00f1or''' ({{IPAc-en|\u02cc|v|i\u02d0|j|\u0259|s|\u026a|n|\u02c8|j|\u0254\u02d0r}} {{respell|VEE|y\u0259|sin|YOR}}<!-- birthdates require citations -->) is an American actress, stand-up comedian, impressionist, visual artist and singer.  She is a cast member on ''[[Saturday Night Live]]'', having joined in the [[Saturday Night Live (season 42)|forty-second season]] in 2016.<ref name=\"impressions\">{{cite news |last=Wilstein |first=Matt |url= http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2016/09/12/snl-s-first-latina-cast-member-melissa-villasenor-is-an-impression-machine.html |title=SNL's First Latina Cast Member Melissa Villase\u00f1or Is an Impression Machine |work=[[The Daily Beast]] |date=September 12, 2016 |accessdate=October 1, 2016}}</ref> Her other credits include voice work on several episodes of ''[[OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes]]'' and ''[[Adventure Time]]'' and a contestant on the sixth season of ''[[America's Got Talent]]''.\n\n==Early life==\nVillase\u00f1or grew up in [[Whittier, California]], and attended the Catholic [[Ramona Convent Secondary School]] in [[Alhambra, California]].<ref>http://www.metro.us/entertainment/tv/snl-melissa-villasenor</ref> She is of [[Mexican]] descent.<ref name=\u201cHuff\u201d>{{cite web|last1=Blay|first1=Zeba |title=First 'SNL' Latina Cast Member Caught Deleting Racist Tweets |url=https://www.huffpost.com/entry/first-snl-latina-cast-member-caught-deleting-racist-tweets|website=HuffPost|accessdate=November 4, 2019 |date=September 23, 2016}}</ref><ref name=Andrews20160913>{{cite web|last1=Andrews|first1=Travis M.|title=Melissa Villase\u00f1or, of 'America's Got Talent' fame, becomes SNL's first Latina cast member|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/morning-mix/wp/2016/09/13/melissa-villasenor-becomes-snls-first-latina-cast-member/|website=[[The Washington Post]]|accessdate=November 24, 2019 |date=September 23, 2016}}</ref> At fifteen, Villase\u00f1or started stand-up at the Laugh Factory Comedy Camp in [[Hollywood|Hollywood, California]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Staff|title=Melissa Villasenor|url=https://www.usanetwork.com/firstimpressions/cast/melissa-villase%C3%B1or|website=USA Network|publisher=USA Network|accessdate=4 April 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nVillase\u00f1or was a semi-finalist in [[America's Got Talent (season 6)|season 6]] of ''[[America's Got Talent]]''.<ref name=Andrews20160913 /> Previously, she was selected for the New Faces lineup in the 2010 [[Just for Laughs]] Montreal Comedy Festival. She has also done voice work for the animated shows ''[[Adventure Time]]'', ''[[Family Guy]]'' and ''[[TripTank]]''.<ref name=\"newest\">{{cite news |last=Slead |first=Evan |url= https://www.ew.com/article/2016/09/12/snl-melissa-villasenor |title=Who is Melissa Villase\u00f1or? Get to know SNL's newest cast member |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |date=September 12, 2016 |accessdate=October 1, 2016}}</ref> Villase\u00f1or appeared on the second season of HBO's ''[[Crashing (U.S. TV series)|Crashing]]''.<ref name=\"White20180226\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.cpluscomedy.com/reviews/2018/2/26/naca-crashing-review |title=\"NACA\" Crashing Review |last=White |first=Chad |date=February 26, 2018 |website=C+ Comedy |access-date=November 24, 2019 |ref=Crashing Season 2 \"NACA\"}}</ref>\n\n===''Saturday Night Live''===\nVillase\u00f1or was introduced as a featured player on the October 1, 2016, episode of ''SNL'' alongside [[Mikey Day]] and [[Alex Moffat (comedian)|Alex Moffat]].<ref name=\"Evans20161002\" /> Her debut was an impression of [[Sarah Silverman]] in the \"Family Feud: Celebrity Edition\" sketch.<ref name=\"Evans20161002\">{{Cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2016/10/snl-debut-newcomers-mikey-day-alex-moffat-melissa-villasenor-1201829645/ |title='SNL' Surprise: Newcomers Mikey Day, Alex Moffat & Melissa Villase\u00f1or Actually Make Good, Strong Impressions |last=Evans |first=Greg |date=October 2, 2016 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |access-date=November 24, 2019}}</ref> Villase\u00f1or is the second Latina cast member after [[No\u00ebl Wells]], who is a quarter Mexican,<ref>https://www.laweekly.com/snl-hires-its-first-latina-cast-member-and-shes-from-l-a/ [[LA Weekly]]</ref> and the first Latina to be promoted to repertory status.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/veronicavillafane/2016/09/30/snl-starts-new-season-with-debut-of-first-latina-cast-member-latino-writer-and-lin-manuel-miranda/ |title=SNL Starts New Season With Debut Of First Latina Cast Member, Latino Writer And Lin-Manuel Miranda |last=Villafa\u00f1e |first=Veronica |date=September 30, 2016 |website=[[Forbes]] |access-date=March 21, 2017}}</ref> She was promoted to the cast of repertory players in [[Saturday Night Live (season 44)|season 44]].<ref name=\"Blair20180929\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.npr.org/2018/09/29/652610008/a-top-impressionist-melissa-villase-or-is-finding-her-own-voice-on-snl |title=A Top Impressionist, Melissa Villase\u00f1or Is Finding Her Own Voice On 'SNL' |last=Blair |first=Elizabeth |date=2018-09-29 |website=[[NPR]] |series=[[Weekend Edition Saturday]] |access-date=November 24, 2019}}</ref>\n\nShe had previously auditioned for the show in [[ Saturday Night Live (season 35)|2009]], when she was just 21 years old. She did a few impressions but was not hired that year. Instead, [[Nasim Pedrad]] and [[Jenny Slate]] were hired.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=wvXadyYrVbY |title=Ep 12 - Comedy and Depression &#124; SNL's Melissa Villasenor |date=March 10, 2016 |website=[[YouTube]] |publisher=The Gray Escape |access-date=November 24, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nAfter Villase\u00f1or became a cast member of ''[[SNL]]'' in 2016, she deleted tweets she had previously written that some viewed as [[racist]]. Most of the tweets uncovered by media publications had been posted in 2010 and 2011. Villase\u00f1or wrote tweets such as, \"A bossy black lady at my temp looks exactly like [[Steve Urkel|steve erkel]]. Ugly\". ''SNL'' and Villase\u00f1or declined to comment on the alleged [[racism]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2016/09/snl-cast-member-melissa-villasenor-deleted-racist-tweets-controversy-1201730304/ |title='SNL's' Latina Cast Member Controversy: Melissa Villase\u00f1or Deleted Racist Tweets |date=September 24, 2016 |website=[[IndieWire]] |access-date=November 24, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/marcusjones/melissa-villasenor-racist-tweets |title=The First Latina \"SNL\" Cast Member Has Been Deleting Offensive Tweets |last=Jones |first=Marcus |date=September 22, 2016 |website=[[BuzzFeed News]] |access-date=November 24, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\u201cHuff\u201d/>\n\nVillase\u00f1or has defended her tweets as \"trying to be edgy,\" and said she didn't regret the deletions.<ref name=\"Blair20180929\" /> In 2018, she told Elizabeth Blair on ''[[Weekend Edition Saturday]]'', \"I'm flawed like everyone else, and yeah, I just wanted to make sure I was perfect.\"<ref name=\"Blair20180929\" />\n\n==Celebrity impressions==\nVillase\u00f1or describes herself as a comedian and impressionist.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.melissavillasenor.com/new-page/|title=Impressions|work=melissavillasenor.com|publisher=}}</ref> She performed various impressions for ''[[America's Got Talent]]'', as well as on ''[[First Impressions (2016 TV series)|First Impressions]]'' and her [[YouTube]] channel, including:\n{{colbegin}}\n* [[Barbara Walters]]<ref name=\"youtube1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?list=PLbtKZM37rkHLat74ZaCxhHE61QuyTlDk-&v=vuQoQMzfG48|title=Celebrity Impressions - Melissa Villasenor - America's Got Talent Audition - Season 6|last=America's Got Talent|date=June 7, 2011|publisher=|via=YouTube}}</ref>\n* [[Natalie Portman]]<ref name=\"youtube1\"/>\n* [[Owen Wilson]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?list=PLbtKZM37rkHLgB163mNr-uPCz3QtlMsfB&v=VdCsbcx_loI|title=Owen Wilson - Daily Itineraries ft. Melissa Villase\u00f1or|author=M\u00e1s Mejor|date=February 10, 2016|publisher=|via=YouTube}}</ref>\n* [[Jennifer Lopez]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=O4v3iTgslB8&index=1&list=PLbtKZM37rkHLgB163mNr-uPCz3QtlMsfB|title=Jennifer Lopez - Daily Itineraries ft. Melissa Villase\u00f1or|last=M\u00e1s Mejor|date=June 8, 2016|publisher=|via=YouTube}}</ref>\n* [[Kristen Wiig]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=y9u6rcAhRa4&list=PLbtKZM37rkHLgB163mNr-uPCz3QtlMsfB&index=2|title=Kristen Wiig - Daily Itineraries ft. Melissa Villase\u00f1or|last=M\u00e1s Mejor|date=May 25, 2016|publisher=|via=YouTube}}</ref>\n* [[Hillary Clinton]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TJZSVmHwKQs&list=PLbtKZM37rkHLgB163mNr-uPCz3QtlMsfB&index=3|title=Hillary Clinton - Daily Itineraries ft. Melissa Villase\u00f1or|last=M\u00e1s Mejor|date=January 20, 2016|publisher=|via=YouTube}}</ref>\n* [[Gwen Stefani]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0NjO2qdCal0&index=4&list=PLbtKZM37rkHLgB163mNr-uPCz3QtlMsfB|title=Gwen Stefani - Daily Itineraries ft. Melissa Villase\u00f1or|last=M\u00e1s Mejor|date=January 27, 2016|publisher=|via=YouTube}}</ref>\n* [[Sonia Sotomayor]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3Z7RJgQAwvc&index=6&list=PLbtKZM37rkHLgB163mNr-uPCz3QtlMsfB|title=Sonia Sotomayor - Daily Itineraries ft. Melissa Villase\u00f1or|last=M\u00e1s Mejor|date=February 3, 2016|publisher=|via=YouTube}}</ref>\n* [[Whitney Cummings]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=v5R7uRT-js4|title=Whitney Cummings has caught me! - Melissa Villase\u00f1or|last=Melissa Villase\u00f1or|date=March 9, 2015|publisher=|via=YouTube}}</ref>\n* [[Sia Furler|Sia]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UCESG06Vta8|title=Sia