raph]] |date=15 June 2000}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"prosecution\">{{cite news |last1=Madden |first1=Andrew |title=PSNI clear 10 of 317 paramilitary-style 'punishment' attacks |url=https://www.irishnews.com/news/2017/06/27/news/psni-clear-10-of-317-paramilitary-style-punishment-attacks-1067594/ |accessdate=27 November 2019 |work=The Irish News |date=27 June 2017 |language=en}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"taskforce\">{{cite news |last1=Kearney |first1=Vincent |title=New taskforce to tackle paramilitaries |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-northern-ireland-41407322?ns_mchannel=social&ns_campaign=bbc_news_ni&ns_source=twitter&ns_linkname=northern_ireland |accessdate=1 December 2019 |work=[[BBC News]] |date=27 September 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n\n===Sources===\n====Books====\n{{refbegin|35em|indent=yes}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Brooks |first1=Graham |title=Criminal Justice and Corruption: State Power, Privatization and Legitimacy |date=2019 |publisher=Palgrave Macmillan |location=Basingstroke |isbn=978-3-030-16038-8 |language=en|ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Feenan |first1=Dermot |title=Informal Criminal Justice |date=2002a |publisher=[[Ashgate Publishing]]|ref=harv|location=Farnham |isbn=978-0-7546-2220-8 |language=en|chapter=Community Justice in Conflict: Paramilitary Punishment in Northern Ireland|pp=41\u201360}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Gallaher |first1=Carolyn |title=After the Peace: Loyalist Paramilitaries in Post-Accord Northern Ireland |date=2011 |publisher=Cornell University Press |location=Ithaca |isbn=978-0-8014-6158-3 |language=en|ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Gormally |first1=Sin\u00e9ad |editor1-last=Pickard |editor1-first=Sarah |title=Anti-Social Behaviour in Britain: Victorian and Contemporary Perspectives |date=2014 |publisher=Palgrave Macmillan |location=Basingstoke |isbn=978-1-137-39931-1 |pages=179\u2013191 |ref=harv |language=en|chapter=The Complexities, Contradictions and Consequences of Being 'Anti-social' in Northern Ireland}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hamill |first1=Heather|au