ky Gervais Live 4: Science]]'' || Stand-up special\n|-\n| 2011 || ''[[68th Golden Globe Awards]]'' || Himself (host) || Television special\n|-\n| 2011\u20132013 || ''[[Life's Too Short (TV series)|Life's Too Short]]'' || rowspan=\"2\" | Himself || 7 episodes; also co-creator, writer, director and executive producer\n|-\n| 2011 || ''[[Curb Your Enthusiasm]]'' || Episode: \"The Hero\"\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2012 || ''[[69th Golden Globe Awards]]'' || Himself (host) || Television special\n|-\n| ''[[Family Guy]]'' || Billy Finn (voice) || Episode: \"[[Be Careful What You Fish For]]\"\n|-\n| 2012\u20132014 || ''[[Derek (TV series)|Derek]]'' || Derek Noakes || 14 episodes; also creator, writer, director and executive producer\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2015 || ''[[Galavant]]'' || Xanax || Episode: \"Dungeons and Dragon Lady\"\n|-\n| ''[[BoJack Horseman]]'' || Hedgehog Orphanage Manager (voice) || Episode: \"[[Out to Sea (BoJack Horseman)|Out to Sea]]\"\n|-\n| 2016 || ''[[73rd Golden Globe Awards]]'' || Himself (host) || Television special\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2018 || ''[[Child Support (game show)|Child Support]]'' || rowspan=\"2\" | Himself || Also creator and executive producer\n|-\n| ''[[Ricky Gervais: Humanity]]'' || Stand-up special\n|-\n| 2019\u2013present || ''[[After Life (TV series)|After Life]]'' || Tony Johnson || Also creator, writer, director and executive producer\n|-\n|2019\n|''[[Scooby-Doo and Guess Who?]]''\n|Himself (voice)\n|Episode: \"Ollie Ollie In-Come Free!\"\n|-\n|2020\n|''[[77th Golden Globe Awards]]''\n|Himself (host)\n|Television special\n|}\n\n===Video games===\n{{BLP unsourced section|date=July 2019}}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n|- \n| 2006 || ''[[Scarface: The World Is Yours]]'' || Englishman\n|-\n| 2008 || ''[[Grand Theft Auto IV]]'' || Himself \n|-\n| 2009 || ''[[Night at the Museum: Battle of the Smithsonian (video game)|Night at the Museum: Battle of the Smithsonian]]'' || Dr. McPhee \n|}\n\n== Stand-up tours ==\n{{BLP unsourced section|date=July 2019}}\n''SuperNature'' is the sixth stand up comedy tour by British comedian Ricky Gervais. The tour will be recorded live and will be a released as a [[Netflix]] exclusive special, similar to his previous tour ''Humanity'' which was released in 2018.\n\n===Tour Dates===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Date\n! City\n! Venue\n|-\n| 13 May 2019\n| [[York]], [[United Kingdom]]\n| [[Barbican Centre, York]]\n|-\n| 14 May 2019\n| [[York]], [[United Kingdom]]\n| [[Barbican Centre, York]]\n|-\n| 4 June 2019\n| [[Newcastle upon Tyne|Newcastle]], [[United Kingdom]]\n| [[Newcastle City Hall]]\n|-\n| 5 June 2019\n| [[Newcastle upon Tyne|Newcastle]], [[United Kingdom]]\n| [[Newcastle City Hall]]\n|-\n| 19 June 2019\n| [[Portsmouth]], [[United Kingdom]]\n| [[Portsmouth Guildhall]]\n|-\n| 20 June 2019\n| [[Portsmouth]], [[United Kingdom]]\n| [[Portsmouth Guildhall]]\n|-\n| 26 June 2019\n| [[Cardiff]], [[United Kingdom]]\n| [[Motorpoint Arena Cardiff]]\n|-\n| 27 June 2019\n| [[Cardiff]], [[United Kingdom]]\n| [[Motorpoint Arena Cardiff]]\n|-\n| 5 July 2019\n| [[Amsterdam]], [[Netherlands]]\n| [[AFAS Live]]\n|-\n| 6 July 2019\n| [[Amsterdam]], [[Netherlands]]\n| [[AFAS Live]]\n|-\n| 16 November 2019\n| [[Madrid]], [[Spain]]\n| Palacio Municipal de Congresos de Madrid\n|-\n| 24 November 2019\n| [[Paris]], [[France]]\n| [[Olympia (Paris)]]\n|}\n\n===DVD / Netflix releases===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Notes\n! Shows\n|-\n| 2003 || ''[[Animals (2003 film)|Animals]]'' || DVD release || {{n/a}}\n|-\n| 2004 || ''[[Politics (2004 film)|Politics]]'' || DVD release || {{n/a}}\n|-\n| 2007 || ''[[Fame (2007 film)|Fame]]'' || DVD release || {{n/a}}\n|-\n| 2009 || ''[[Science (film)|Science]]'' || DVD release || 32 shows\n|-\n| 2017\u20132018 || ''Humanity'' || [[Netflix]] Exclusive || 146 shows\n|-\n| 2019\u20132020 || [[SuperNature]] || [[Netflix]] Exclusive || TBD\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wiki