itish men podcasters]]\n[[Category:English radio DJs]]\n[[Category:English satirists]]\n[[Category:English screenwriters]]\n[[Category:English social commentators]]\n[[Category:English stand-up comedians]]\n[[Category:English television directors]]\n[[Category:English television producers]]\n[[Category:English television writers]]\n[[Category:LGBT rights activists from the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Berkshire]]\n[[Category:Male new wave singers]]\n[[Category:Male television writers]]\n[[Category:Outstanding Performance by a Lead Actor in a Comedy Series Primetime Emmy Award winners]]\n[[Category:People from Reading, Berkshire]]\n[[Category:Primetime Emmy Award winners]]\n[[Category:Secular humanists]]\n[[Category:Showrunners]]\n[[Category:Social critics]]\n[[Category:Writers Guild of America Award winners]]\n", "name_user": "Jsvgegrhgh", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ricky_Gervais"}
{"title_page": "Solstice (British metal band)", "text_new": "{{About|the UK doom metal band|other uses|Solstice (disambiguation)}}\n{{Multiple issues|{{Notability|Music|date=June 2011}}\n{{refimprove|date=October 2009}}\n{{lead too short|date=December 2009}}\n}}\n{{Use British English|date=July 2016}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2016}}\n{{Infobox musical artist| <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject Musicians -->\n| name                = Solstice\n| image                 =\n| caption            =\n| image_size            =\n| background          = group_or_band\n| alias               =\n| origin              = [[Bradford]], [[West Yorkshire]], [[England]], [[United Kingdom|U.K.]]\n| genre               = [[Epic doom metal]]<ref name=Zero>{{cite web |last1=VIRTANEN |first1=MIIKA |title=SOLSTICE ANNOUNCE NEW VOCALIST |url=http://www.ztmag.com/blog/news/solstice-announce-new-vocalist/ |website=[[Zero Tolerance (magazine)|Zero Tolerance]] |accessdate=22 July 2018}}</ref> \n| years_active        = 1990\u2013present\n| label               =\n| associated_acts     = [[Sore Throat (grindcore band)|Sore Throat]], Isen Torr, Wartorn, Warfear, The Lamp Of Thoth, Arcane Sun, Discontrol, [[My Dying Bride]]\n| website                 = {{URL|http://solstice-englander.blogspot.com/}}\n| current_members     = Hagthorn<br>Richard M. Walker<br>James Ashbey<br>Andy Whittaker<br>Ian \"Geezer\" Buxton\n| past_members        = Paul Bwitton<br>Rick Budby<br>Brendan Dawson<br>Morris Ingram<br>Simon Matravers<br>Chaz Netherwood<br>[[Tom Phillips (musician)|Tom Phillips]]<br>[[Gian Pyres]]<br>Gary Riley<br>Lennaert Roomer<br>Mark Stojsavljevic<br>[[Hamish Glencross]]<br>[[Shaun Taylor-Steels]]<br>Lenny Robinson<br>Paul Thomas Kearns\n}}\n\n'''Solstice''' is an [[epic doom metal]] band from Dewsbury, England, founded by Rich Walker after the breaking up of his previous [[hardcore punk]] / [[grindcore]] bands [[Sore Throat (grindcore band)|Sore Throat]] and [[Warfear]].\n\nRich Walker also used to run The Miskatonic Foundation, a record label dedicated to doom metal and traditional heavy metal. It has now since dissolved due to lack of time.{{Citation needed|date=December 2017}}\n\n==History==\n\nThe band released their debut album ''Lamentations'' on England's [[Candlelight Records]] in 1994 and caught the attention of an underground scene that was at that point swept up with the still new second wave of black metal. Successive UK and European tours, with Count Raven and Anathema respectively, firmly cemented the band as something of a cult act across the continent.\n\n1996 saw the release of the ''Halcyon'' EP on Black Tears, comfortably conveying the strength and progression of that line-up, while further embracing their English Heavy Metal roots but with an aesthetic that shows the band were not afraid to court a more sinister undercurrent. Shortly after, however, Solstice once again suffered line-up problems that essentially resulted in the band becoming largely dormant. In 1998, the band signed with [[Misanthropy Records]], which helped with the release of ''New Dark Age'', but the band was painfully laid to rest in 2002.\n\nIn 2007, Solstice was re-ignited. after a five-year hiatus, Walker commented that he was inspired to continue Solstice after enlisting the services of Andrew Whittaker from The Lamp Of Thoth.{{Citation needed|date=September 2012}}The recruitment of Paul Bwitton on vocals and Richard Horton on drums (both formerly of NWOBHM outfit Scarab) proved fruitless, but undeterred the band had Procession singer Felipe temporarily fill the vocalist position in order to honour live commitments.\n\nBuoyed by this success, Solstice set about recruiting a full-time vocalist with whom they could move forward and so in the Summer of 2011 they welcomed Paul Thomas Kearns into the lineup. An Irishman living in Oslo, Kearns had appeared on one album with disbanded Irish Doom/Death Metal outfit [[Arcane Sun]]. The new line-up of Solstice made their live debut supporting [[Primordial (band)|Primordial]] in the latter's 20 years anniversary show at Dublin's Academy on 24 September 2011. Del Nichol replaced Richard Horton on drums later in 2011 and was also replaced nine months later by Deceptor's drummer James Ashbey.\n\nSolstice ended their 12-year absence from the recording studio in early 2013 with the release of their Mini LP ''Death's Crown is Victory'',  issued on their own \"White Horse\" imprint. They promoted this release by touring across Europe.\n\nIn late 2019, Hel Thorne, alternately regarded as Hagthorn, was revealed as the new vocalist of Solstice, having replaced Paul Thomas Kearns.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://theobelisk.net/obelisk/2019/12/04/solstice-new-singer/|title=Solstice Add New Vocalist; Demo Tracks Posted|website=The Obelisk|date=4 December 2019|accessdate=8 January 2020}}</ref> To commemorate her joining the band, Solstice released a two-song EP called ''White Thane'', which consisted of two songs from their 2018 album ''White Horse Hill'' reworked with Hagthorn on vocals.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://solstice-englander.bandcamp.com/album/white-thane|title=White Thane|website=Solstice [[Bandcamp (website)|Bandcamp]]}}</ref> Hagthorn's previous musical experience includes being the vocalist for [[Vermont]]-based doom metal band Chalice.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://metalstorm.net/events/news_comments.php?news_id=37233|title=Solstice - Welcome New Vocalist|website=[[Metalstorm.net]]|date=7 December 2019|accessdate=9 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n\n===Albums===\n* ''[[Lamentations (Solstice album)|Lamentations]]'', 1994\n* ''New Dark Age'', 1998\n* ''White Horse Hill'', 2018\n\n===Mini Albums===\n*''[[Death's Crown Is Victory]]'', 2013\n*''[[White Horse Hill]]'', 2015\n\n===EPs===\n* ''Halcyon'', 1996<ref>[http://www.discogs.com/artist/Solstice+%282%29 Solstice (2)] discogs.com. Retrieved on 2011-01-02.</ref>\n\n===Splits===\n* ''Solstice/Twisted Tower Dire'', 2001\n* ''Solstice/The Lord Weird Slough Feg'', 2002\n\n===Demos===\n* ''Lamentations'', 1991\n* ''MCMXCII'', 1992\n* ''As Empires Fall'', 1993\n* ''Ragnarok'', 1994\n* ''Drunken Dungeon Sessions'', 1997\n* ''To Sol A Thane'', 2016\n\n===Compilations===\n* ''Only the Strong'', 2008\n* ''Epicus Metalicus Maximus'', 2010<ref>[http://www.bnrmetal.com/v2/bandpage.php?ID=Sols Solstice] bnrmetal.com. Retrieved on 2011-01-02.</ref>\n\n==Band members==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n;Current members\n* Hagthorn - vocals\n* Richard M. Walker - guitar\n* James Ashbey - drums\n* Andy Whittaker - guitar\n* Ian \"Geezer\" Buxton - bass\n{{col-2}}\n;Former members\n* Rick Budby &ndash; drums\n* Brendan Dawson &ndash; bass\n* Morris Ingram &ndash; vocals\n* [[Simon Matravers]] &ndash; vocals\n* Chaz Netherwood &ndash; bass\n* [[Tom Phillips (musician)|Tom Phillips]] &ndash;vocals\n* [[Gian Pyres]] &ndash; guitar\n* Gary Riley &ndash; drums\n* Lennaert Roomer &ndash; drums\n* Mark Stojsavljevic &ndash; vocals\n* Hamish Glencross &ndash; lead guitar\n* Shaun \u2018Winter\u2019 Taylor-Steels &ndash; drums\n* Lenny Robinson &ndash; bass<ref name=Zero/>\n* Paul Thomas Kearns - vocals\n{{col-end}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.myspace.com/solsticeenglander Solstice myspace]\n* [http://www.miskatonic.cc/band_sol.html Official Solstice page at The Miskatonic Foundation]\n* [http://www.metal-archives.com/band.php?id=718 Solstice at Encyclopedia Metallum]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Solstice (Uk Band)}}\n[[Category:English doom metal musical groups]]\n[[Category:Musical groups established in 1990]]\n", "text_old": "{{About|the UK doom metal band|other uses|Solstice (disambiguation)}}\n{{Multiple issues|{{Notability|Music|date=June 2011}}\n{{refimprove|date=October 2009}}\n{{lead too short|date=December 2009}}\n}}\n{{Use British English|date=July 2016}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2016}}\n{{Infobox musical artist| <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject Musicians -->\n| name                = Solstice\n| image                 =\n| caption            =\n| image_size            =\n| background          = group_or_band\n| alias               =\n| origin              = [[Bradford]], [[West Yorkshire]], [[England]], [[United Kingdom|U.K.]]\n| genre               = [[Epic doom metal]]<ref name=Zero>{{cite web |last1=VIRTANEN |first1=MIIKA |title=SOLSTICE ANNOUNCE NEW VOCALIST |url=http://www.ztmag.com/blog/news/solstice-announce-new-vocalist/ |website=[[Zero Tolerance (magazine)|Zero Tolerance]] |accessdate=22 July 2018}}</ref> \n| years_active        = 1990\u2013present\n| label               =\n| associated_acts     = [[Sore Throat (grindcore band)|Sore Throat]], Isen Torr, Wartorn, Warfear, The Lamp Of Thoth, Arcane Sun, Discontrol, [[My Dying Bride]]\n| website                 = {{URL|http://solstice-englander.blogspot.com/}}\n| current_members     = Hagthorn<br>Richard M. Walker<br>James Ashbey<br>Andy Whittaker<br>Ian \"Geezer\" Buxton\n| past_members        = Paul Bwitton<br>Rick Budby<br>Brendan Dawson<br>Morris Ingram<br>Simon Matravers<br>Chaz Netherwood<br>[[Tom Phillips (musician)|Tom Phillips]]<br>[[Gian Pyres]]<br>Gary Riley<br>Lennaert Roomer<br>Mark Stojsavljevic<br>[[Hamish Glencross]]<br>[[Shaun Taylor-Steels]]<br>Lenny Robinson<br>Paul Thomas Kearns\n}}\n\n'''Solstice''' is an [[epic doom metal]] band from Dewsbury, England, founded by Rich Walker after the breaking up of his previous [[hardcore punk]] / [[grindcore]] bands [[Sore Throat (grindcore band)|Sore Throat]] and [[Warfear]].\n\nRich Walker also used to run The Miskatonic Foundation, a record label dedicated to doom metal and traditional heavy metal. It has now since dissolved due to lack of time.{{Citation needed|date=December 2017}}\n\n==History==\n\nThe band released their debut album ''Lamentations'' on England's [[Candlelight Records]] in 1994 and caught the attention of an underground scene that was at that point swept up with the still new second wave of black metal. Successive UK and European tours, with Count Raven and Anathema respectively, firmly cemented the band as something of a cult act across the continent.\n\n1996 saw the release of the ''Halcyon'' EP on Black Tears, comfortably conveying the strength and progression of that line-up, while further embracing their English Heavy Metal roots but with an aesthetic that shows the band were not afraid to court a more sinister undercurrent. Shortly after, however, Solstice once again suffered line-up problems that essentially resulted in the band becoming largely dormant. In 1998, the band signed with [[Misanthropy Records]], which helped with the release of ''New Dark Age'', but the band was painfully laid to rest in 2002.\n\nIn 2007, Solstice was re-ignited. after a five-year hiatus, Walker commented that he was inspired to continue Solstice after enlisting the services of Andrew Whittaker from The Lamp Of Thoth.{{Citation needed|date=September 2012}}The recruitment of Paul Bwitton on vocals and Richard Horton on drums (both formerly of NWOBHM outfit Scarab) proved fruitless, but undeterred the band had Procession singer Felipe temporarily fill the vocalist position in order to honour live commitments.\n\nBuoyed by this success, Solstice set about recruiting a full-time vocalist with whom they could move forward and so in the Summer of 2011 they welcomed Paul Thomas Kearns into the lineup. An Irishman living in Oslo, Kearns had appeared on one album with disbanded Irish Doom/Death Metal outfit [[Arcane Sun]]. The new line-up of Solstice made their live debut supporting [[Primordial (band)|Primordial]] in the latter's 20 years anniversary show at Dublin's Academy on 24 September 2011. Del Nichol replaced Richard Horton on drums later in 2011 and was also replaced nine months later by Deceptor's drummer James Ashbey.\n\nSolstice ended their 12-year absence from the recording studio in early 2013 with the release of their Mini LP ''Death's Crown is Victory'',  issued on their own \"White Horse\" imprint. They promoted this release by touring across Europe.\n\nIn late 2019, Hel Thorne, alternately regarded as Hagthorn, was revealed as the new vocalist of Solstice, having replaced Paul Thomas Kearns.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://theobelisk.net/obelisk/2019/12/04/solstice-new-singer/|title=Solstice Add New Vocalist; Demo Tracks Posted|website=The Obelisk|date=4 December 2019|accessdate=8 January 2020}}</ref> To commemorate her joining the band, Solstice released a two-song EP called ''White Thane'', which consisted of two songs from their 2018 album ''White Horse Hill'' reworked with Hagthorn on vocals.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://solstice-englander.bandcamp.com/album/white-thane|title=White Thane|website=Solstice [[Bandcamp (website)|Bandcamp]]}}</ref> Hagthorn's previous musical experience includes being the vocalist for [[Vermont]]-based doom metal band Chalice.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://metalstorm.net/events/news_comments.php?news_id=37233|title=Solstice - Welcome New Vocalist|website=[[Metalstorm.net]]|date=7 December 2019|accessdate=9 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n\n===Albums===\n* ''[[Lamentations (album)|Lamentations]]'', 1994\n* ''New Dark Age'', 1998\n* ''White Horse Hill'', 2018\n\n===Mini Albums===\n*''[[Death's Crown Is Victory]]'', 2013\n*''[[White Horse Hill]]'', 2015\n\n===EPs===\n* ''Halcyon'', 1996<ref>[http://www.discogs.com/artist/Solstice+%282%29 Solstice (2)] discogs.com. Retrieved on 2011-01-02.</ref>\n\n===Splits===\n* ''Solstice/Twisted Tower Dire'', 2001\n* ''Solstice/The Lord Weird Slough Feg'', 2002\n\n===Demos===\n* ''Lamentations'', 1991\n* ''MCMXCII'', 1992\n* ''As Empires Fall'', 1993\n* ''Ragnarok'', 1994\n* ''Drunken Dungeon Sessions'', 1997\n* ''To Sol A Thane'', 2016\n\n===Compilations===\n* ''Only the Strong'', 2008\n* ''Epicus Metalicus Maximus'', 2010<ref>[http://www.bnrmetal.com/v2/bandpage.php?ID=Sols Solstice] bnrmetal.com. Retrieved on 2011-01-02.</ref>\n\n==Band members==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n;Current members\n* Hagthorn - vocals\n* Richard M. Walker - guitar\n* James Ashbey - drums\n* Andy Whittaker - guitar\n* Ian \"Geezer\" Buxton - bass\n{{col-2}}\n;Former members\n* Rick Budby &ndash; drums\n* Brendan Dawson &ndash; bass\n* Morris Ingram &ndash; vocals\n* [[Simon Matravers]] &ndash; vocals\n* Chaz Netherwood &ndash; bass\n* [[Tom Phillips (musician)|Tom Phillips]] &ndash;vocals\n* [[Gian Pyres]] &ndash; guitar\n* Gary Riley &ndash; drums\n* Lennaert Roomer &ndash; drums\n* Mark Stojsavljevic &ndash; vocals\n* Hamish Glencross &ndash; lead guitar\n* Shaun \u2018Winter\u2019 Taylor-Steels &ndash; drums\n* Lenny Robinson &ndash; bass<ref name=Zero/>\n* Paul Thomas Kearns - vocals\n{{col-end}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.myspace.com/solsticeenglander Solstice myspace]\n* [http://www.miskatonic.cc/band_sol.html Official Solstice page at The Miskatonic Foundation]\n* [http://www.metal-archives.com/band.php?id=718 Solstice at Encyclopedia Metallum]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Solstice (Uk Band)}}\n[[Category:English doom metal musical groups]]\n[[Category:Musical groups established in 1990]]\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links toLamentations (disambiguation)(link changed toLamentations (Solstice album)) usingDisamAssist.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Solstice_(British_metal_band)"}
